related_questions.question: How do I get a job in New York state?
related_questions.snippet: To start your search for a state job, browse through currently scheduled exams or upcoming exams....Visit the State Jobs Website.Select For the General Public.Click Vacancies on the left side of the page.Select a job title and read through the job specifics.If you qualify, follow the instructions on how to apply.

related_questions.question: Do you have to live in NYC to work for NYC?
related_questions.snippet: U.S. Citizenship: For most jobs, you do not need to be a citizen. All applicants must be legally authorized to work in the United States and will be required to submit proof of eligibility. Residency: Requirements vary by job although the majority of jobs require that you live in New York City.
